.cs 7 on
.item '$SET BLOCK Command' 'Added on 07/25/82 by LSO'
.boxon
$SET BLOCK {DAY|EVENING|NIGHT|WEEKEND}
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
Required Privileges:  SYSTEMS

The $SET BLOCK command allows you to change the current time block.

.* SELECT 'SAVE Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION DAY,EVENING,NIGHT,WEEKEND
.optix DAY
.optix EVENING
.optix NIGHT
.optix WEEKEND
{DAY|EVENING|NIGHT|WEEKEND}
\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\The time blocks are divided as follows:
                  DAY        Monday - Friday    6 am to 6 pm
                  EVENING    Monday - Friday    6 pm to 10 pm
                  NIGHT      Monday - Thursday 10 pm to 6 am,
                             Friday            10 pm to midnight
                  WEEKEND    Friday midnight to Monday 6 am
.cs 7 off
